 <p>WildWand MerryTale<BR> Conjurer<BR>Short On Hair, Big On Nose</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1180<br> <font color=#333333>(4/1/02 3:45:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=210.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Krilen is not anti mage</span><hr size=1> Although I disagree with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Krilen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, he has a definite opinion, makes an interesting proposal, and I for one have learned a few things from the discussion that has resulted from his radical proposal.  His idea is worthy of discussion, which is why I copied from another thread where it was buried and moved it to the top level where it could be discussed.<br>
<br>
There are several important points that he makes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Casters are not dependent on gear, nor do they improve by gear.  Therefore, the gap between the best and worst equipped casters is much less than the gap between the best and worst equipped melees.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
This point had been largely missed in discussions of caster-melee imbalance.  While most everybody, myself included, emphasized the ability to twink melees with equipment, and the poor quality of caster loot in comparison to melee, loot independence for casters was taken for granted.  That is, we complained about not getting the benefit of equipment, but ignored the fact that casters benefit from not really needing it much in the first place.<br>
<br>
In other words, the fact that caster loots sucks does not itself suck as much as it might appear.<br>
<br>
While I am still in favor of some improvements for caster loots, it is now clear to me that the best caster gear should improve casters less than the best melee gear improves melees.<br>
<br>
I did not learn this until the discussion of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Weak Non-Focused Pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Pets are overpowered.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Maybe.  There are a spectrum of opinions regarding pet power.  Some say they suck, others think they are adequate or nearly so.  Others say the issue is not power, but availability and risk.  Just because <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Krilen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'s is a minority opinion, does not make him anti-Mage.<br>
<br>
He may even be right.  Too many <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> dismiss or take for granted the utility of having an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elemental</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> on call for the price of a few hundred mana and a malachite.  I suspect that with the exception of risk of trains, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elementals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are far better than most <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are willing to acknowledge.  In general, players of a particular class tend take their own abilities for granted, while emphasizing the abilities of other classes which they lack.<br>
<br>
It also brings up an important question.  Just exactly how do you demonstrate that pets are either underpowered or overpowered?  While DPS can be revealing, I think it is not by itself generally sufficient.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Pet strength should depend on enchancements.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Not unreasonable.  As I have written elsewhere, the ability to chain cast pets puts strong limits on increases in raw pet power.  I am of the opinion that any significant improvements in pet power should be in the form of external pet enhancements, such as buffs, or dropped or summoned pet only items.<br>
<br>
I find many flaws in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Krilen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'s proposal.  It is radical, costly, and has no clear benefits.  It has the appearance of being motivated by self interest, and would punish casual players.  It lacks compelling arguments or evidence in its favor.  It also has the distinct appear of singling out <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for punishment, as many of the argument he puts forward apply to casters in general, yet he avoids that conclusion.<br>
<br>
It is not well argued, in other words.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Stated more weakly, less radically, and with trade offs, something similar could have been proposed like this:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> likely considers pets overpowered or close to it.  The existance of chain-casting means that raw improvements in pet power are unlikely, and the current level of raw pet power gives little room for over all improvement.<br>
<br>
I propose that in order to make pets scale better as players rise in power, that raw pet power be reduced somewhat, and more power concentrated in focus-type items.  This gives more scope for improvements in pet power without encouraging chain casting or AFK experience.  Further, a variety of pet focus items at varying power levels would make for more worthwhile <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> loot and help to distinguish accomplished <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
What does not work is:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> ...nerf pets into oblivion, and force casters to hold focus items...Weak as hell with no items, powerful with items...Any idiotic loser mage...you want to be more powerful then you are now, and don't want to do anything for it. I cannot respect that...If you're too lazy to get your focus items...Personally, I think I should be more powerful than you...I want pets nerfed...merely by leveling to 60 the caster has earned the right to be as powerful as a warrior who has levelled to 60 and done extreme things yeilding extreme loot<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->The language incites more than it convinces.  It undermines the very points <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Krilen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is trying to make.<br>
<br>
In conclusion, let me make one thing <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;perfectly clear.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  I learn far more from people I disagree with than people who already agree with me.<br>
<br>
If I did not think what <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Krilen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> had to say was important, I would not have moved it to a top level thread.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
